values:
I haven't posted anything in a long while... I guess it's a combination of being busy, not wanting to, and forgetting.&nbsp; 

I guess my biggest news at the moment is that I have been pre-approved for a mortgage for a place that I love.&nbsp; It isn't built yet... but I've seen the same unit already and it is just perfect.&nbsp; It is a duplex and I get to pick out all of the finishes.&nbsp; While I'm horrified of living alone, I'm excited at the prospect of having something I can say is mine.&nbsp; 

My job is going just great.&nbsp; I was on call the last two nights and I have a ridiculous cold, but&nbsp;I didn't get called in so essentially I got paid to toss and turn in bed.&nbsp; They hired another ultrasound tech so the call is even more split up now!&nbsp; My abdominal registry exam is a week from today... hopefully it will be my last.&nbsp; My health insurance has kicked in and my retirement fund is growing!

My ferret is totally cute.&nbsp; She is pretty tame and lets me hold her all of the time.&nbsp; Annoyingly, she doesn't quite have the litter box thing down, but it doesn't make too much of a mess nor does it smell.&nbsp; She sleeps in her hammock and inside a plush octopus.&nbsp; She's the cutest little bandita ever!

I've started acquiring furniture for my new place!&nbsp;&nbsp;It is a ton of fun to pick out appliances and things.&nbsp; Too bad it costs so darn much!&nbsp;&nbsp;Those lucky people who got married first... I envy your registries! &nbsp;

Ah, well.&nbsp; I hope everyone else has had an enjoyable summer!&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been left at home while everyone else goes camping/water skiing... with the dog.&nbsp; Joyous.

My first Christmas on my own was not all I cracked it up to be.&nbsp; I kept insisting to myself that I would not miss my family... but when Kelli woke me up very early for presents I stayed in bed after she left and cried.&nbsp; She was not Alex.&nbsp; She was not Jim.&nbsp; Hell, her family even goes about opening presents all wrong.&nbsp; They had the same thing for dinner as they did on Thanksgiving!&nbsp; Toss things up a bit, people!&nbsp; But really, they are great people and I was very happy to be with them; it's just that it wasn't the same, see?&nbsp; 

Rock Band is my new favorite thing.&nbsp; Kelli sings, her brother John is on drums and I've got guitar.&nbsp; Any random Joe who comes over gets to be bass.&nbsp; Our characters are HOT and we can play for hours and not even notice that time has flown by!&nbsp; 

I finally got health insurance.&nbsp; Whoopee.&nbsp; It has done me no bloody good.&nbsp; There are no primary physicians in this area accepting new patients at this time.&nbsp; Hell, come to find out a couple nights ago my insurance DOESN'T EVEN COVER WHAT I GOT IT FOR!&nbsp; They give a general overview of their coverage when you are picking one out and it made no mention of this, so when I cracked open the 93743979 page book and found the page on it I was devastated.&nbsp; Damn this whole system!&nbsp; New Mexico hates me!

So we're moving (yes, this means me too).&nbsp; House is supposedly going on the market in January.&nbsp; I'm still not that thrilled, but I can't help but catch Kelli's excitement about the whole thing.&nbsp; There is a job prospect for me... so we'll see how that pans out.&nbsp; For now we're redoing practically everything in the house.&nbsp; Oh joy.&nbsp; Pulling up tile, painting, cleaning, boxing and packing.&nbsp; Just what I want to do after working 60 hours a week.&nbsp; Oh well.&nbsp; Picking out houses online is kind of fun.

Chalk another one up for stress.&nbsp; I'm retaking my abdominal registry in less than a week and if I pass I:&nbsp; 1. Become registered.&nbsp; 2.&nbsp; Get a $3 p/h raise.&nbsp; And 3.&nbsp; Never have to freaking study again.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oh, the peace of mind.

I'm going to be home alone the 27th-10th so if anyone wants to just hop on down to visit (lol) or call that would be great.&nbsp; It's going to get hella lonely, especially on the 4th, which has always been my favorite holiday and family time.

I'm officially coming home July 20-30th.&nbsp; Can't wait to see the Michigan again!&nbsp; Kelli will be coming up, too!&nbsp; (27-30th.)&nbsp; WEEE!&nbsp; 

We saw 1408 yesterday and both enjoyed it.&nbsp; Kelli earned herself a sleeping partner because of it.&nbsp; It was genuinely creepy without being morbid or slasher-nasty.&nbsp; 





Hope everyone is doing well.&nbsp; I just dyed my hair RED so I'll get some pictures soon.&nbsp; New job has been going just all right.&nbsp; Not as many hours as I had hoped and it is kind of boring.&nbsp; Oh well.&nbsp;&nbsp; It is money, and after I get back from visiting home I'll look for something else.&nbsp;

After a couple days the novelty has worn off, but I'm still excited to be making money again.&nbsp; I work for TransRay Diagnostic, a mobile diagnostic imaging service, and so far I've gotten to see a lot more of this city than I ever thought I would.&nbsp; My hours are 9-between 4 and 5 Mon-Thurs.&nbsp; That is a schedule I cannot complain about.&nbsp; On top of that, I get to set my own patient schedule, so if someone calls for an ultrasound I get to tell them when/which day.&nbsp; I have a cute little laptop portable machine that I get to bring home if I want.&nbsp; Over the weekend Kelli and I inspected all of our bits (she has a huge thyroid nodule, not sure how she didn't feel it before).&nbsp; The people are all super goofy and loads of fun.&nbsp; This should do very well for now!&nbsp; Plus once I pass my abdominal boards I get a $3p/h raise.&nbsp; Wee!

Wicked in Denver ROCKED!&nbsp; I was actually more excited for Kelli to see it for the first time because I knew how much she would love it and that really made it worth-while.&nbsp; Of course she had a "stomach issue" Saturday morning so we didn't get to shop or anything but oh well.&nbsp; If anyone is ever in the Denver area be sure to check out Vesta's Dipping Grill.&nbsp; YUMMY!!!!!!&nbsp; 

It sounds as if I will be in Michigan July 20-30 to see my brother before he heads off to his first USAF station in Alaska for two years.&nbsp; I really can't wait to see green again!&nbsp; And my kitty... and my family.&nbsp; And perhaps Kelli will join me up there for a couple of days.&nbsp; 

There is a large labradoodle staring at me with anticipating eyes.&nbsp; Better go play with her...

Abdominal boards tomorrow morning at 8AM.&nbsp; One could say this is the culmination of my entire educational career coming to a head less than 24 hours from now.&nbsp; The last six months of studying had best pay off.

STREEESSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS.

Kelli had an ultrasound done this morning - really stresses me out that I couldn't do it for her.&nbsp; I don't want random Joes/Josies who don't give a damn just breezing through it.&nbsp; Same goes for anyone I know!&nbsp;

Another sunny Monday in Albuquerque.&nbsp; Too bad I just got an official rejection in the mail from my dream job.&nbsp; I did, however, get a job offer as a receptionist in a vet's office.&nbsp; It's a very serene place and it's off the beaten trail in a cool area of New Mexico so I'm kind of excited that if I have to "settle" for a job for the time being this will be okay.&nbsp; 

My brother is leaving in about a week for the USAF.&nbsp; It makes me sad that he's going somewhere where I can't protect him anymore.&nbsp; Not that I could really do it from here, anyway... but that's not the point.&nbsp; It's nice to know that I'll see him online every once in a while and get to chat; when he goes away I'm going to miss him so much.&nbsp; 

ZOMG I got my ears pierced.&nbsp; What kind of a girly girl am I becoming?!?!?!?!

I lost enough weight to go down a pants size and not feel too fat in tank tops!&nbsp; Hurray!&nbsp; 


Lonliness has set in and the realization that I have no one to call up and go out for dinner with has become very real.&nbsp; No lunch dates, no drinks with friends, no DDR parties.&nbsp; It really sets in when Kelli goes out with her family... who will take me out for birthday dinner?&nbsp; Who will celebrate with me when I finally do get a "real" job down here?&nbsp; I threw a pity party for myself on Saturday.&nbsp; I'll get over it.

So... as some of you may know I've been studying hardcore for my abdominal registry exam.&nbsp; I filled out my application and paid the $200 for it on the first of the month.&nbsp; I still hadn't gotten my exam confirmation letter thing so I called today to see why.&nbsp; Apparently when you apply online there's a popup frame when you're finished with the application that tells you if you need to send anything in... and also apparently the ARDMS website is not fully Mozilla friendly.... and so when there was no frame I assumed I had to send nothing in.&nbsp; But that's not true, says the lady I talked to today.&nbsp; My "clinical verification form" that I used in October for physics was supposed to be good for a year, and it is... BUT the tech who signed it for me is registered in OB/gyn and not in ABD so I'm out my money.&nbsp; And they didn't tell me that.&nbsp; And now I just wasted a month.&nbsp; And I still don't have a job.&nbsp; And I cried when I got off of the phone.&nbsp; *sigh*

Oh a personally happier note... my WoW guild is starting a new instance tonight for the first time and Kelli and I are both really excited about it.&nbsp; What a pathetic existence!&nbsp; 

"Music and Lyrics" was just meh as far as romantic comedies go, I wouldn't waste the $6.&nbsp; 



Any volunteers to come to New Mexico to hug me?&nbsp; Pretty please?
